FBIS4-24150 "drafr122_c_94013" FBIS-AFR-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Ramaphosa Seeking Constitutional Experts for Assembly Ramaphosa Seeking Constitutional Experts for Assembly MB2306164294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1500 GMT 23 Jun 94 MB2306164294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The Constitutional Assembly, which is to draw up South Africa's final constitution over the next two years, is to ask for nominations by the end of next month for a panel of constitutional experts to advise it. Constitutional Assembly Chairman Cyril Ramaphosa said in Cape Town it would then be able to start sifting through the nominations during the August session of Parliament.
